For a complete understanding of the objects, techniques and structure of the invention reference should be made to the following detailed description and accompanying drawings wherein:


FIG. 1 is a side elevational view in partial cross section illustrating a prior art electromagnetic drum brake;


FIG. 2 is a side elevational view of the caliper disk brake for steel mill cranes according to the invention;


FIG. 3 is a top plan view of the caliper disk brake of FIG. 2;


FIG. 4 is a cross sectional view of the coil and armature assembly of the caliper disk brake of FIGS. 2 and 3;


FIG. 5 is a top plan view of a caliper disk wear pad;


FIG. 6 is a cross sectional view of the caliper disk wear pad showing its split configuration;


FIG. 7 is an exploded cross sectional view of a sealed and lubricated trunion bushing employed in the invention;


FIG. 8 is an exploded view of a center spring and button used in the invention to align the armatures with the electromagnetic coil; and


FIG. 9 is a cross sectional view of a trunion employed in the caliper disk brake of the invention.
